
Aim

To identify and define the core use cases of the Predictive Stock Management System that describe the interactions between actors and the system.

Identified Core Use Cases
1. Login to System

Actors: Admin, Store Manager, Inventory Staff
Description: Allows authorized users to securely access the system.

2. Manage User Accounts

Actors: Admin
Description: Enables the admin to create, update, and remove user accounts and assign roles.

3. Record Sales Data

Actors: Sales System, Inventory Staff
Description: Captures daily sales transactions for analysis and prediction.

4. Update Inventory Levels

Actors: Inventory Staff
Description: Updates stock quantities when items are sold or received.

5. View Stock Levels

Actors: Store Manager, Inventory Staff
Description: Displays real-time inventory status for all products.

6. Predict Stock Demand

Actors: Store Manager, Prediction Engine
Description: Uses historical sales data to forecast future stock requirements.

7. Generate Restock Alerts

Actors: System
Description: Automatically notifies users when stock falls below threshold levels.

8. Place Restock Order

Actors: Store Manager
Description: Initiates restocking requests based on system predictions.

9. Manage Supplier Details

Actors: Admin
Description: Maintains supplier information and contact details.

10. Generate Reports

Actors: Admin, Store Manager
Description: Produces sales, inventory, and prediction reports for analysis and decision-making.

Use Case Summary Table
Use Case ID	Use Case Name	Primary Actor(s)
UC-01	Login to System	Admin, Manager, Staff
UC-02	Manage User Accounts	Admin
UC-03	Record Sales Data	Sales System, Staff
UC-04	Update Inventory Levels	Inventory Staff
UC-05	View Stock Levels	Manager, Staff
UC-06	Predict Stock Demand	Manager, System
UC-07	Generate Restock Alerts	System
UC-08	Place Restock Order	Manager
UC-09	Manage Supplier Details	Admin
UC-10	Generate Reports	Admin, Manager
Result

Ten core use cases were identified to represent the key functionalities of the Predictive Stock Management System.

Conclusion

Defining core use cases helps in understanding system behavior and user interactions. The Predictive Stock Management Systemâ€™s use cases cover inventory control, prediction, and reporting functionalities.
